It doesn't kill as fast as lava, but you'll get more Gunpowder because none of it is being destroyed.

text: IMPORTANT NOTES ABOUT MOB FARMS: It's not height 120, its +120 from wherever your spawning chamber is. If you build your spawning chamber at 50, then you wanna go up to 170. The idea behind optimizing mob farms is you want everything else in the caves below and the surrounding area to despawn so that all the spawning happens in the spawning chamber. By going up 120, you're far away enough from stuff that they despawn. To ensure best rates for any type of mob farm, you actually wanna build up in the sky so all the mobs are forced to spawn in the chamber youve created. Ground ones can still work tho. Best rates are gonna be in the day time where no mobs spawn in the overworld except in really dark areas (i.e. a mob farm). If other people are logged on, preferably you want them to be in the afk area with you so that they don't cause things to spawn and hurt your rates. Hope this was helpful :D

text:
Just a reminder/clarification:
You have to AFK on the platform because only a specific amount of hostile mobs can exist at a time (Mob Cap) and once the Mob Cap is filled up, no more new mobs can spawn. You want the mob cap to be as low as possible to make a farm as efficient as possible. 
Mobs can only spawn in a128 block radius around the player so If you AFK above the farm with the surface around it lit up via torches, you eliminate the spawns of mobs in underground caves and increase the efficiency of the farm.
